# Redux Toolkit Code Standards & Best Practices

> This document defines the recommended standards and architectural guidelines for using Redux Toolkit (RTK) in this codebase. All generated code should follow these conventions.

---

# Core Principles

- Use Redux Toolkit (`@reduxjs/toolkit`) exclusively.
- Avoid legacy Redux patterns (`createStore`, manual reducers, action constants).
- Prefer RTK Query for server state.
- Use Redux only for shared application state.
- Keep Redux state serializable.
- Keep Redux state minimal.
- Derive data using selectors instead of storing computed values.
- Favor feature-based organization over technical-layer organization.

---

# Recommended Project Structure when using Redux

```text
src/
├── app/
│   ├── store.ts
│   └── hooks.ts
│
├── features/
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── authSlice.ts
│   │   ├── authSelectors.ts
│   │   ├── authThunks.ts
│   │   └── types.ts
│   │
│   ├── users/
│   │   ├── usersSlice.ts
│   │   ├── usersSelectors.ts
